ort | Men's [[judo]] }}\n{{MedalCountry | {{NED}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[Olympic Games]] }}\n{{MedalBronze | [[2008 Summer Olympics|2008 Beijing]] | [[Judo at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 100 kg|\u2013100 kg]] }}\n{{MedalBronze | [[2012 Summer Olympics|2012 London]] | [[Judo at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 100 kg|\u2013100 kg]] }}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[World Judo Championships|World Championships]] }}\n{{MedalSilver | [[2009 World Judo Championships|2009 Rotterdam]] | [[2009 World Judo Championships \u2013 Men's 100 kg|\u2013100 kg]] }}\n{{MedalSilver | [[2010 World Judo Championships|2010 Tokyo]] | [[2010 World Judo Championships \u2013 Men's 100 kg|\u2013100 kg]] }}\n{{MedalSilver | [[2013 World Judo Championships|2013 Rio de Janeiro]] | [[2013 World Judo Championships \u2013 Men's 100 kg|\u2013100 kg]] }}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[European Games]] }}\n{{MedalGold | [[Judo at the 2015 European Games|2015 Baku]] | \u2013100 kg }}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2019 European Games|2019 Minsk]]|[[Judo at the 2019 European Games \u2013 Men's +100 kg|+100 kg]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[European Judo Championships|European Championships]] }}\n{{MedalGold | [[2008 European Judo Championships|2008 Lisbon]] | \u2013100&nbsp;kg }}\n{{MedalSilver | [[2009 European Judo Championships|2009 Tbilisi]] |\u2013100&nbsp;kg }}\n{{MedalSilver | [[2010 European Judo Championships|2010 Vienna]] | \u2013100&nbsp;kg }}\n{{MedalSilver | [[2013 European Judo Championships|2013 Budapest]] | \u2013100&nbsp;kg }}\n{{MedalGold | [[2015 European Judo Championships|2015 Baku]] | \u2013100&nbsp;kg }}\n{{MedalGold | [[2016 European Judo Championships|2016 Kazan]] | \u2013100&nbsp;kg }}\n{{MedalBronze | [[2018 European Judo Championships|2018 Tel Aviv]] | +100&nbsp;kg }}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2019 European Judo Championships|2019 Minsk]]|+100 kg}}\n\n| show-medals      = yes\n| updated          = 26 November 2018\n}}\n\n'''Hindrik Harmannus Arnoldus \"Henk\" Grol''' (born 14 April 1985 in [[Veendam]]) is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[judoka]].\n\n==Judo career==\n\nGrol competed in the [[2007 European Judo Championships]] in Belgrade, Serbia in the men's under 90&nbsp;kg, as a replacement for [[Mark Huizinga]], who cancelled last minute due to personal problems.\n\nHe won gold in the men's under 100-kilo class at the [[2008 European Judo Championships]] in Lisbon, Portugal. He was the youngest European Champion of that year, only 22 years old.\n\nAfter a highly competitive race against [[Elco van der Geest]], Grol ended up to be the 2008 representative for the men's 100&nbsp;kg category for the [[Netherlands]] at the 2008 Olympics in Beijing. There he reached the semifinals, where he was beaten by [[Askhat Zhitkeyev]] from [[Kazakhstan]]. He went on to win bronze.\n\nHe competed at the [[2012 Summer Olympics]], reaching the quarter-finals, where he lost to [[Dimitri Peters]] of Germany.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web |title=90 \u2013 100kg (half-heavyweight) men results \u2013 Judo \u2013 London 2012 Olympics |url=http://www.olympic.org/olympic-results/london-2012/judo/90-100kg-half-heavyweight-m |website=www.olympic.org |accessdate=2015-11-02}}</ref>  Grol went on to win the bronze medal beating [[Ramziddin Sayidov]] in his bronze medal match.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nHe competed at the [[2018 European Judo Championships]] in [[Tel Aviv]] where he ended third. <ref>https://www.combat-sports.net/en/2018/05/04/judo-henk-grol-now-i-felt-physically-stronger/</ref>\n\n==Outside of Judo==\nAfter the [[2016 Olympics]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]] he considered starting a [[mixed martial arts]] career and trained with [[Gegard Mousasi]] in [[Amsterdam]]. Eventually he decided to quit training MMA due to safety considerations.<ref>http://www.mmaplanet.nl/mmanieuws/henk-grol-overwoog-mma-maar-dat-werd-niets/</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n* [http://www.judoinside.com/judoka/14777 Profile] on Judoinside.com\n* [http://www.judoinside.com/judoka/view/14777/judo-videos Videos of Henk Grol] on JudoInside.com\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Grol, Henk}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Dutch male judoka]]\n[[Category:European Games competitors for the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:European Games gold medalists for the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:European Games medalists in judo]]\n[[Category:Judoka at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Judoka at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Judoka at the 2016 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Judoka at the 2015 European Games]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic bronze medalists for the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Olympic judoka of the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in judo]]\n[[Category:People from Veendam]]\n[[Category:Judoka at the 2019 European Games]]\n[[Category:European Games bronze medalists for the Netherlands]]\n\n\n{{Netherlands-judo-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Dutch judoka}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name             = Henk Grol\n| headercolor      = \n| image            = Henk Grol with his bronze medal at the 2012 summer Olympics (cropped).JPG\n| image_size       = \n| caption          = Grol in 2012\n| birth_name       = \n| fullname         = Hindrik Harmannus Arnoldus Grol\n| nickname         = \n| nationality      = [[Netherlands|Dutch]]\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1985|4|14}}\n| birth_place      = [[Winschoten]], Netherlands\n| death_date       = \n| death_place      = \n| residence        = [[Haarlem]], [[Netherlands]]\n| education        = Communications, Marketing\n| alma_mater       = Johan Cruijff College\n| height           = {{convert|1.90|m|ftin|abbr=on}}\n| weight           = {{convert|110|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}}\n| website          = {{URL|henkgrol.nl}}\n| country          = [[Netherlands]]\n| sport            = [[Judo]]\n| event            = 100 kg\n| club             = Kenamju\n| turnedpro        = \n| coach            = Maarten Arens, Ronald Joorse\n| retired          = \n| coaching         = \n| worlds           = {{unbulleted list\n | '''[[2010 World Judo Championships|2010 Tokyo]]''': [[2010 World Judo Championships \u2013 Men's 100 kg|-100 kg]] \u2013 Silver\n}}\n| regionals        = {{unbulleted list\n | '''[[2008 European Judo Championships|2008 Lisbon]]''': 100 kg \u2013 Gold\n | '''[[2008 European Judo Championships|2009 Tbilisi]]''': 100 kg \u2013 Silver\n}}\n| nationals        = \n| olympics         = {{unbulleted list\n | '''[[Judo at the 2008 Summer Olympics|2008 Beijing]]''': [[Judo at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 100 kg|-100 kg]] \u2013 Bronze\n | '''[[Judo at the 2012 Summer Olympics|2012 London]]''': [[Judo at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 100 kg|-100 kg]] \u2013 Bronze\n}}\n| paralympics      = \n| highestranking   = \n| pb               =\n| medaltemplates   = \n{{MedalSport | Men's [[judo]] }}\n{{MedalCountry | {{NED}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[Olympic Games]] }}\n{{MedalBronze | [[2008 Summer Olympics|2008 Beijing]] | [[Judo at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 100 kg|-100 kg]] }}\n{{MedalBronze | [[2012 Summer Olympics|2012 London]] | [[Judo at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 100 kg|-100 kg]] }}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[World Judo Championships|World Championships]] }}\n{{MedalSilver | [[2009 World Judo Championships|2009 Rotterdam]] | [[2009 World Judo Championships \u2013 Men's 100 kg|-100 kg]] }}\n{{MedalSilver | [[2010 World Judo Championships|2010 Tokyo]] | [[2010 World Judo Championships \u2013 Men's 100 kg|-100 kg]] }}\n{{MedalSilver | [[2013 World Judo Championships|2013 Rio de Janeiro]] | [[2013 World Judo Championships \u2013 Men's 100 kg|-100 kg]] }}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[European Games]] }}\n{{MedalGold | [[Judo at the 2015 European Games|2015 Baku]] | \u2013100 kg }}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2019 European Games|2019 Minsk]]|[[Judo at the 2019 European Games \u2013 Men's +100 kg|+100 kg]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[European Judo Champion