-02}}</ref>  Grol went on to win the bronze medal beating [[Ramziddin Sayidov]] in his bronze medal match.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nHe competed at the [[2018 European Judo Championships]] in [[Tel Aviv]] where he ended third. <ref>https://www.combat-sports.net/en/2018/05/04/judo-henk-grol-now-i-felt-physically-stronger/</ref>\n\n==Outside of Judo==\nAfter the [[2016 Olympics]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]] he considered starting a [[mixed martial arts]] career and trained with [[Gegard Mousasi]] in [[Amsterdam]]. Eventually he decided to quit training MMA due to safety considerations.<ref>http://www.mmaplanet.nl/mmanieuws/henk-grol-overwoog-mma-maar-dat-werd-niets/</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n* [http://www.judoinside.com/judoka/14777 Profile] on Judoinside.com\n* [http://www.judoinside.com/judoka/view/14777/judo-videos Videos of Henk Grol] on JudoInside.com\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Grol, Henk}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Dutch male judoka]]\n[[Category:European Games competitors for the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:European Games gold medalists for the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:European Games medalists in judo]]\n[[Category:Judoka at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Judoka at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Judoka at the 2016 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Judoka at the 2015 European Games]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic bronze medalists for the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Olympic judoka of the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in judo]]\n[[Category:People from Veendam]]\n[[Category:Judoka at the 2019 European Games]]\n[[Category:European Games bronze medalists for the Netherlands]]\n\n\n{{Netherlands-judo-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Jonas kam", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henk_Grol"}
{"title_page": "Barani Institute of Sciences", "text_new": "The '''Barani Institute of Sciences''' ([[Urdu]]: {{nq|\u0628\u0627\u0631\u0627\u0646\u06cc \u0627\u0646\u0633\u0679\u06cc\u0679\u06cc\u0648\u0679 \u0622\u0641 \u0633\u0627\u0626\u0646\u0633\u0632}}), or '''BIS''' is a private institute having its campuses in [[Sahiwal]] and [[Burewala]].<ref name=\":0\" /> It is affiliated with [[Pir Mehr Ali Shah Arid Agriculture University|Pir Mehr Ali Shah Arid Agriculture University, Rawalpindi]].<ref name=\":1\" />{{Infobox university\n| name            = Barani Institute of Sciences\n| native_name = {{nq|\u0628\u0627\u0631\u0627\u0646\u06cc \u0627\u0646\u0633\u0679\u06cc\u0679\u06cc\u0648\u0679 \u0622\u0641 \u0633\u0627\u0626\u0646\u0633\u0632}}\n| other_name      = Barani Institute of Sciences, JV of PMAS Arid Agriculture University RWP. University, Rawalpindi\n| established     = 2014\n| affiliation     =[[Pir Mehr Ali Shah Arid Agriculture University]]\n| city            = [[Sahiwal]], [[Burewala]]\n| province        = [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]]\n| country         = [[Pakistan]]\n| website         = {{URL|baraniinstitute.edu.pk}}\n| image_name      = Barani_Institute_of_Sciences.png \n}}\n{{Infobox university\n | name        = Sahiwal Campus\n | native_name = {{nq|\u0628\u0627\u0631\u0627\u0646\u06cc \u0627\u0646\u0633\u0679\u06cc\u0679\u06cc\u0648\u0679 \u0622\u0641 \u0633\u0627\u0626\u0646\u0633\u0632\u060c \u0633\u0627\u06c1\u0650\u064a\u0648\u0627\u0644\u200e}}\n | other_name  = Barani Institute of Sciences Sahiwal Campus, JV of PMAS Arid Agriculture University RWP.\n | address     = 520 B/VII, Jail Road\n | city        = [[Sahiwal]]\n | director    = Dr. Azeem Ahmed\n | province    = [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]]\n | country     = [[Pakistan]]\n | image_name  = Barani_Institute_of_Sciences,_Sahiwal.png \n | footnotes   = Barani Institute of Sciences, Sahiwal.\n}}\n{{Infobox university\n | name        = Burewala Campus\n | native_name = {{nq|\u0628\u0627\u0631\